<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870522-0128 </DOCNO><HL> Corrections andamp; Amplifications:Montana</HL><DD> 05/22/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><TEXT>   MONTANA has an annual season for hunting bighorn sheep. It also auctions off one bighorn permit annually to raise money for sheep research and wild sheep improvement programs; this year the high bid was $109,000. An earlier edition incorrectly described the state's program and gave an incorrect figure for the high bid.    (See: &quot;The Game Is at Stake as Wardens Combat a Plague of Poachers --- Foes Range From 'River Rat' to Hunters in Helicopters And Agent's Best Friend&quot; -- WSJ May 4, 1987) </TEXT></DOC>